Eskola Cirque (80°43′S23°49′W﻿ / ﻿80.717°S 23.817°W) is a cirque 2 nautical miles (4 km) wide between Arkell Cirque and Bowen Cirque in the central Read Mountains of the Shackleton Range, in [MASK].

In association with the names of geologists grouped in this area, it was named by the UK [MASK] Place-Names Committee in 1971 after Pentti Eskola, a Finnish geologist who was an authority on the Precambrian rocks of Finland and on silicate melt systems.

Morgan Peak (75°47′S68°24′W﻿ / ﻿75.783°S 68.400°W) is a peak rising to about 1,100 metres (3,600 ft), located 3 nautical miles (6 km) northeast of Mount Leek in the Hauberg Mountains of Palmer Land, [MASK].

Eurydice Peninsula (Bulgarian: полуостров Евридика, ‘Poluostrov Eurydice’ po-lu-'os-trov e-vri-'di-ka) is the predominantly ice-covered 8 km wide peninsula projecting from Danco Coast, [MASK] Peninsula 7.4 km northwestwards into Charlotte Bay south of Recess Cove.
Andrée Island (64°31′S61°31′W﻿ / ﻿64.517°S 61.517°W) is an island lying in Recess Cove, Charlotte Bay, off the north coast of Eurydice Peninsula, Danco Coast on the [MASK] Peninsula.
First View Point (77°1′S163°3′E﻿ / ﻿77.017°S 163.050°E) is a small point between Cape Roberts and Avalanche Bay in Granite Harbour, Victoria Land, [MASK].

Graovo Rocks (Bulgarian: скали Граово, ‘Skali Graovo’ ska-'li 'gra-o-vo) is the group of rocks off the north coast of Robert Island in the South Shetland Islands, [MASK], situated east of Lientur Rocks and southwest of Liberty Rocks, and extending 1.75 km (1.09 mi) in north-south direction and 750 m (820 yd) in east-west direction.
Flint Glacier (67°20′S65°25′W﻿ / ﻿67.333°S 65.417°W) is a glacier which flows south into Whirlwind Inlet between Demorest Glacier and Cape Northrop, on the east coast of Graham Land, [MASK].

Lockley Point (64°47′S63°23′W﻿ / ﻿64.783°S 63.383°W) is a low, ice-covered point lying 1 nautical mile (2 km) northeast of Noble Peak on the northwest side of Wiencke Island, in the Palmer Archipelago, [MASK].
Milosz Point is a low-lying, ice-free cape on the northern coast of King George Island, the largest of the South Shetland Islands of [MASK].

Borima Bay (Bulgarian: залив Борима, ‘Zaliv Borima’ 'za-liv 'bo-ri-ma) is the 6.5 km wide cove indenting for 8 km Oscar II Coast in Graham Land, [MASK] south of Diralo Point and north of Caution Point.

Kresna Gully (Kresnenska Padina 'kre-snen-ska pa-'di-na) is a heavily crevassed depression in Perunika Glacier extending 2.25 km westwards from Rezen Knoll in eastern Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands, [MASK].
Millington Glacier is a narrow tributary glacier, 10 nautical miles (19 km) long, flowing from the eastern slopes of the Hughes Range, [MASK], into Ramsey Glacier, northward of Mount Valinski.

Stravinsky Inlet (72°20′S71°30′W﻿ / ﻿72.333°S 71.500°W) is an ice-covered inlet lying between Shostakovich Peninsula and Monteverdi Peninsula in southern Alexander Island, [MASK].
